{"uid":"79ae4cb9eba8c635","name":"[BUG-OT-005] TC-OT-013 — PUT /api/v1/token: Must return 405 Method Not Allowed (returns 500)","fullName":"oauth-token-spr-fetcher-api.spec.ts:662:7","historyId":"d7d124f66b6b7d328bc1bca20e40694e:e4acb582e721a659464b17d63ea876ab","time":{"start":1783444792869,"stop":1783444853105,"duration":60236},"description":"**[KNOWN BUG — BUG-OT-005]**\n\n**What this test does:**\nSends a PUT request to /api/v1/token (which is a GET-only endpoint) and verifies the server responds with 405 Method Not Allowed.\n\n**Expected:** HTTP 405 Method Not Allowed with an Allow header listing the valid methods\n**Actual:** HTTP 500 Internal Server Error\n\n**Root Cause:** The service throws an unhandled exception instead of returning a proper 405 response when it receives an unsupported HTTP method.\n\n**Impact:** API clients that probe method availability or send the wrong method receive a confusing 500 error instead of a clear 405 with the Allow header. This also indicates unhandled exception paths that could mask real server errors.","descriptionHtml":"<p><strong>[KNOWN BUG — BUG-OT-005]</strong></p>\n<p><strong>What this test does:</strong><br />\nSends a PUT request to /api/v1/token (which is a GET-only endpoint) and verifies the server responds with 405 Method Not Allowed.</p>\n<p><strong>Expected:</strong> HTTP 405 Method Not Allowed with an Allow header listing the valid methods<br />\n<strong>Actual:</strong> HTTP 500 Internal Server Error</p>\n<p><strong>Root Cause:</strong> The service throws an unhandled exception instead of returning a proper 405 response when it receives an unsupported HTTP method.</p>\n<p><strong>Impact:</strong> API clients that probe method availability or send the wrong method receive a confusing 500 error instead of a clear 405 with the Allow header. This also indicates unhandled exception paths that could mask real server errors.</p>\n","status":"passed","flaky":false,"newFailed":false,"newBroken":false,"newPassed":false